  "title": "Barista/Front of House",
  "description": "<p>Position: Barista / Front of House<br>\nType: Full-Time (5-day work week, inclusive of weekends &amp; public holidays)</p>\n<p>​</p>\n<p>At Acoustics Coffee Bar, we believe great coffee begins with great people. Our Front-of-House team is the heart of the café — creating an inviting atmosphere, connecting with guests, and ensuring every visit feels calm, genuine, and memorable.</p>\n<p>If you’re someone who enjoys good conversations, appreciates the craft of coffee, and takes pride in warm hospitality, we’d love to meet you!</p>\n<h4>What You’ll Do</h4>\n<p>• Deliver friendly and attentive service to every guest<br>\n• Share menu recommendations and product knowledge with confidence<br>\n• Process orders accurately through the POS system<br>\n• Ensure drinks and food are served promptly and beautifully<br>\n• Assist in setting, clearing, and maintaining a clean, welcoming space<br>\n• Support the team during events and busy service periods<br>\n• Communicate customer feedback thoughtfully to the shift manager<br>\n• Uphold hygiene and food safety standards at all times<br>\n• Take on other duties as assigned to support smooth daily operations</p>\n<h4>What We’re Looking For</h4>\n<p>• Passionate about hospitality, service, and coffee culture<br>\n• A positive, self-motivated team player<br>\n• Excellent communication and interpersonal skills<br>\n• Able to multitask and thrive in a fast-paced environment<br>\n• Willing to work on weekends and public holidays<br>\n• No prior experience required — training will be provided<br>\n• 1–2 years in F&amp;B or retail is a plus</p>\n<p>​</p>\n<p>If you find joy in creating calm moments for others, we’d love to have you on our team.</p>",
